**Which 2ct lab pear to choose:**

At D-VVS1, GIA and IGI are identically priced at $2,692. The [GIA D-VVS1 Ideal at $2,692](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28761071?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the correct choice when prices match — GIA global name recognition costs nothing extra here. The upgrade to D-IF (IGI) at $4,941 is $2,249 more than the D-VVS1 entry.

VVS1 is already eye-clean and microscopically flawless in appearance; D-IF's improvement is meaningful only under magnification. The $2,249 is better spent on the setting or retained. The exception: buyers who want a GIA D-IF specifically for documentation prestige should choose [$6,393 GIA D-IF](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23939038?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the premium over IGI D-IF is $1,452.

